abstract: Ken Johnson, a fullback, was among the 11 players whom the New York Giants placed on waivers yesterday, the team announced at its training camp in Pleasantville, N.Y. Six other players were put on the injuredreserve list to reduce the roster to 61. The club said another player would be cut today, when all National Football League teams must be down to the 60-player limit.
CLEVELAND There is no movie house in downtown Cleveland. The last one closed this spring. And the city remains in default on payments it could not meet in 1978.

abstract: MIAMI, Sunday, Aug. 17--Hijackers seized three jetliners yesterday and ordered them to fly to Cuba, according to airline and Federal officials. The hijackings brought to six the number of United States planes commandeered and diverted to Cuba in a week.
